From e017b5f4941ef35390a3068b8357565af82c03ad Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 09:24:11 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 23/39] WIP: media: dvb-frontends: avl6862: fix chip id mapping
 fall-through in avl6862_attach

The switch mapping the raw chip id to a model number lacked break
statements, so every case fell through to the last and id was always
set to 6862 regardless of the detected chip. Add break statements so
each id code maps to its correct model number, which also fixes the
-Wimplicit-fallthrough warnings.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c
index 0d8aeb027f13..9605ab8f6e37 100644
--- a/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c
+++ b/drivers/media/dvb-frontends/avl6862.c
@@ -2031,12 +2031,16 @@ struct dvb_frontend *avl6862_attach(struct avl6862_config *config,
 	switch (id) {
 	case 0xb:
 		id = 6882;
+		break;
 	case 0xd:
 		id = 6812;
+		break;
 	case 0xe:
 		id = 6762;
+		break;
 	case 0xf:
 		id = 6862;
+		break;
 	}
 	dev_info(&priv->i2c->dev,
 		 "%s: found AVL%d "
-- 
